<HEADLINE> Six Children Die in House Fire in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Six children, the youngest
2 years old, were killed Sunday when a fire sent flames and smoke
roaring through the upstairs bedrooms of their grandparents' home
in Detroit, capital of Michigan State of the United States,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Three adults and a 10-year-old child escaped, the reports
quoted local officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
The children, aged 2, 5, 6, 7, 8 and 11, were found in two
bedrooms. Their mother was not at the home. Among the adults who
escaped was the grandmother.
</P>
<P>
Two of the adults who escaped were unharmed. There was no
official word on the condition of the two others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
