<HEADLINE> 555 S. Africans Die in Traffic Accidents Since </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 27 (Xinhua) -- At least 555 people have died
in traffic accidents throughout South Africa since December, Godfrey
Maluleke, spokesman for the traffic department said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 180 drivers, 197 passengers and 178 pedestrians died
in 388 fatal road collisions on South African roads, Maluleke said.
</P>
<P>
The main contributory factors in the acccidents are speed. Most of
the pedestrians who were killed were knocked over by vehicles while
they were walking in the middle of the road under the influence of
alcohol, traffic police said. 
</P>
