influential boat builder who won many U.S. and international
yachting championships, has died at age 87.
</P>
<P>
Etchells designed the Etchells 22. This design is now known as
the International Etchells Class.
</P>
<P>
In the 1940s and the 1950s, Etchells dominated international
competition in the one-design Star Class. In the 1960s, he
created the Etchells 22. He built Stars for 30 years and Etchells
22s for 20 years.
</P>
<P>
He won his first world championship title in 1951 and retired
in 1984. 
