<HEADLINE> Last Session of Nepal's Parliament Set for January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Nepali King Birendra has
called the 15th session of parliament, the last for the present
parliament, for January 13, 1999, the king's Principal Press
Secretariat said in a notice Monday.
</P>
<P>
The major function of the session, usually for passage of
bills, will be to take the confidence vote on the new tri-partite
government led by Girija Prasad Koirala, parliamentary sources
said.
</P>
<P>
