<HEADLINE> 5 Iranians Killed, 10 Injured in Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 28 (Xinhua) -- An explosion occurred on a
fuel tanker of the Iranian navy Sunday afternoon, killing five
crew members and injured 10 others.
</P>
<P>
So far the reason for the incident has not been
established. The tanker anchored at the naval forces jetty in the
southern port Bandar Abass, the Islamic Republic News Agency
(IRNA) reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The injured, who suffered burns, have been sent to hospital and
the fire has been extinguished. 
</P>
