<HEADLINE> China Welcomes Indian Foreign Minister's Speech, FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 28 (Xinhua) -- China has always attached
importance to the growth of its good-neighborly, friendly and
cooperative ties with India on the basis of the Five Principles of
Peaceful Co-existence, Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remark this afternoon when asked to comment on
Indian Foreign Minister Jaswant Singh's recent speech concerning
his dedication to improving India-China relations.
</P>
<P>
Singh in his speech urged the world's two most populous
nations to improve their bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome Foreign Minister Singer's speech," Zhu said, and
the Chinese side hopes that the Indian side will continue to make
effective efforts, so as to bring the bilateral relations between
the two countries back to the track of normal growth as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
"Such a move complies with the fundamental interest of the
people of both countries," Zhu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
