<HEADLINE> Former Zambian President Criticizes Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Former Zambian president
Kenneth Kaunda criticized the government policies in the
country's Northern Province on Sunday, saying that his United
National Independence Party (UNIP) will use the local government
elections as a launch pad for the second liberation of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a rally in Chinsali of the province, Kaunda said he
cannot sit by and let Zambia go to ruins because of misguided
leadership, The Post reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
