<HEADLINE> National Indexes Pass Appraisal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 28 (Xinhua) -- China's wholesale price
indexes for grain and edible oil recently passed an appraisal
conducted by an expert panel from authoritative departments and
universities.
</P>
<P>
The indexes, the first of their kind, cover wholesale prices
for grain and edible oil. They also cover composite wholesale
prices for both grain and oil.
</P>
<P>
The indexes are calculated according to daily pricing
information provided by 39 regional wholesale grain and edible oil
markets, large grain enterprises and grain stocks in major
production and sales centers throughout the nation. Calculations
are made based on June 1994 prices.
</P>
<P>
Zhengzhou grain and edible oil wholesale market, the largest of
its kind in the country, is located in the capital of central
China's Henan Province. A computer network links major wholesale
markets nationwide. 
</P>
