<HEADLINE> Philippine Bankers Group Backs Raising Bank Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 28 (Xinhua) - The Bankers Association of the
Philippines Monday voiced its support for a move of the central
bank to increase the minimum capital requirements of banks in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Deogracias Vistan, president of the association, said in an
interview that there is a strong need to introduce changes in the
minimum capitalization of banks to respond to the currency crisis.
</P>
<P>
As a requirement of the central bank, universal banks in the
country are directed to boost their capital base by 80 percent.
</P>
<P>
The central bank recently also encouraged banks, particularly
those which could not cope with the increase in minimum
capitalization, to consolidate and merge.
</P>
<P>
Vistan described the central bank's move as the best and
meaningful way to strengthen the banking industry's operations.
