<HEADLINE> 20 People Killed in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Twenty people were killed and
161 others injured in 299 road accidents reported in Zimbabwe
between Christmas eve and Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman superintendent Wayne Bvudzijena was quoted by
Monday's The Harare daily as saying that almost 4,000 tickets
were issued to motorists for speeding and other offenses by
police throughout the country during the period.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 22 people were killed in over 400 accidents during
the same period, he said.
</P>
<P>
Police have mounted an extensive campaign to help bring order
to the country's roads during the festive season, including the
deployment of all available manpower from the National Highway
Patrol, according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The Vehicle Inspection Department, the enforcement arm of the
Ministry of Transport and Energy, also deployed officers onto the
roads to help police check on road worthiness of vehicles, he
said. 
