</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- Sri Lanka's earnings from private remittances have
topped 710 million U.S. dollars for the first nine months of this
year, a 12.7 percent growth over the same period last year,
officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Most of these earnings have come from the expatriate
community," said a Foreign Employment Bureau official, adding
that there is an increasing demand for Sri Lankan skilled labor
from many countries.
</P>
<P>
Private remittances have now become a major foreign exchange
earning source for the Sri Lankan economy and the expatriate
community contributes the lion's share of these earnings. (Sri
Lanka-Expatriates)
