<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man Sets Record in Living With Snakes in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 28 (Xinhua) -- A man has set a new
Malaysian record in the number of days living with poisonous
snakes in a special cage.
</P>
<P>
Othman Ayeb, 31, set the record Sunday in Langkawi, a resort
island in northern Malaysia, by staying with poisonous snakes for
21 days, breaking the previous record set by Malaysia's King of
Snakes Hussain Dastagir, who lived with poisonous snakes for 20
days, a press reports said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Othman, known as a snake champion after winning several
competitions at the national and international levels in the past,
began living with 150 poisonous snakes on December 6 at Taman
Lagenda and planned to live with the snakes for 27 days. 
</P>
