<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Major Infrastructure Projects Proceed Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Of the 46 major
infrastructure projects undertaken in Shanghai this year, 12 have
been completed and are now in operation.
</P>
<P>
Combined investment for these projects has approached 50
billion yuan, one-quarter of the city's fixed asset
investment.
</P>
<P>
Government sources said that projects are being carried over
into the new year are proceeding smoothly.
</P>
<P>
At the top of the list of the 12 completed projects is the
General Motors automobile plant which has started rolling cars off
the assembly line.
</P>
<P>
Completion of the first-phase upgrading of the Waigaoqiao
Harbor has raised its annual handling capacity from 490,000
standard containers to 680,000.
</P>
<P>
And completion of the Shanghai-Hangzhou expressway and the
first-phase construction of the outer ring road has improved
transportation in Shanghai as well as the ecological
environment of the city.  
</P>
