<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Highways Exceed 4,000 Kilometers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, the largest
commercial center in China, has built 91 kilometers of highways
this year, bringing its total highway length to 4,051 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has originally planned to spend 4.1 billion yuan on
highway construction this year, but ended up spending 5.78 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
According to official information, highway density in the
city has increased from 0.625 kilometer per square kilometer of
area at the beginning of the year to 0.639 by year's end.
</P>
<P>
Officials said highways will continue to be a focus of
Shanghai's infrastructure construction, and in the next few years
density will be raised to 1 kilometer per square kilometer of
area.  
