<HEADLINE> China Establishes Files for Giant Pandas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese experts have
established files for 37 giant pandas living in the Tangjiahe
Nature Reserve in southwest China's Sichuan Province to monitor
their genetic identity and strengthen the protection of these rare
animals.
</P>
<P>
The files include the total number, sex, and blood
relationships of the giant pandas in the reserve.
</P>
<P>
The Tangjiahe Reserve is located in northern Sichuan's Longmen
Mountain area which neighbors Gansu Province.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that there are some 1,000 giant pandas in the
world, and 80 percent of them live in Sichuan Province. 
</P>
