<HEADLINE> China Launches Massive Water-Control Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 28 (Xinhua) -- China has launched an
unprecedentedly massive campaign to improve its flood-fighting
capabilities after suffering heavy losses from this summer's
severe flooding, according to the China Water Resources News.
</P>
<P>
Since the floods receded in early September, an accumulated
2.89 billion work days have been spent on renovating and upgrading
reservoirs, canals and other facilities.
</P>
<P>
As many as 96 million people work along the rivers, reservoirs
and lakes of China, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 19.4 billion yuan has been invested on these
projects, including 9.71 billion yuan in personal spending by the
farmers, a ten percent increase in their investment over last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
