<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fixed-Assets Investment Growing In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 28 (Xinhua) -- In the first eleven months
this year, fixed-assets investment in this top industrial center
of China reached 126.4 billion yuan (15.2 billion U.S. dollars), a
3.4 percent rise over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Investment in the service sector, 84.4 billion yuan, accounted
for two-thirds of the total, while that in infrastructure
construction hit 39.4 billion yuan, 31.2 percent of all investment.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, investment in real estate dropped by three
percent compared with the same period last year to 36.8 billion
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
